Senior Data Engineer (Python, Spark, TensorFlow) required:

• Ph.D. or equivalent experience in Machine Learning/Data Science and 5+ years of hands-on experience building large-scale data processing pipelines using Python, Apache Spark, and/or TensorFlow;
• Strong understanding of distributed computing framework architecture, including Hadoop, Beam, and AWS Glue;
• Proficiency in designing and developing scalable data storage solutions using relational databases (e.g., MySQL) and NoSQL databases (e.g., Cassandra, MongoDB);
• 3+ years of experience with big data tools like PySpark, scikit-learn, and pandas; familiarity with cloud-based services for ETL processing (e.g., AWS S3, GCS);
• Proven ability to troubleshoot complex data processing issues using logs, performance metrics, and debugging techniques;
• Excellent communication skills for collaborating with distributed teams, including data scientists, engineers, and business stakeholders;
• Willingness to obtain a valid US security clearance (TS/SCI) or existing clearance;
• Experience with GitHub/Bitbucket for version control management; comfortable working in an agile environment with automated testing using Pytest/unittest;

